  "text": "Assume that the natural mapping g ! gl res via the adjoint representation is lifted to a mapping g ! e gl res , where gl res = gl res (g) is a \"restricted\" general linear algebra of the vector space g, for example, the one consisting of operators whose g + ! g , block is of a finite rank; e gl res is a nontrivial central extension of gl res , see e.g., [CITATION_1] . If this lifting is not possible, we should replace g by the corresponding central extension, which will be lifted canonically. Let : g ! C be the linear functional defined by this lifting and a splitting of the extension 0 ! C ! e gl res ! gl res ! 0 as an extension of vector spaces. In fact, this splitting can be chosen in such a way that vanishes on all g n but g 0 , see for example, [CITATION_2] Proposition 2.4 ]. We will assume this for the sake of simplicity.",
